WEBVTT

00:44.280 --> 00:48.200
TURN OF THE TIDE

00:50.320 --> 00:51.560
DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS

01:05.680 --> 01:07.480
Where are they sending you back to?

01:09.560 --> 01:10.440
Georgia.

01:11.400 --> 01:12.960
Country, not the state.

01:15.160 --> 01:16.760
Leave anyone behind?

01:18.880 --> 01:20.160
My son and wife.

01:21.360 --> 01:22.880
I got a fish in my cell.

01:24.520 --> 01:27.280
It's called Red.
Couldn't bring it with me.

01:30.720 --> 01:32.840
Are you comparing
a stupid fish to my family?

01:33.520 --> 01:37.120
Of course not.
Your wife and son can make it without you.

01:37.880 --> 01:39.240
But without me, the fish...

01:40.440 --> 01:42.280
Mmm, I don't think it will make it.

01:42.280 --> 01:44.920
<i>You served seven years in jail</i>

01:44.920 --> 01:47.080
<i>for using explosives in a robbery.</i>

01:48.040 --> 01:50.400
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Anything you want to say?

01:51.240 --> 01:52.800
I have been rehabilitated.

01:52.800 --> 01:56.760
I learned my lesson.
I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

01:56.760 --> 01:59.880
Are you quoting
<i>The Shawshank Redemption</i> to me, Mr. Cunha?

02:00.560 --> 02:01.680
It's a beautiful movie.

02:01.680 --> 02:03.800
Yes, but he was innocent and you're not.

02:04.440 --> 02:07.920
- I'm sending you back to your country.
- This is my country, Your Honor.

02:08.640 --> 02:11.480
You were born in Portugal, Mr. Cunha.

02:11.480 --> 02:14.320
That makes this your adopted country,
where you committed a crime.

02:14.320 --> 02:16.040
And did my time for it.

02:16.640 --> 02:19.160
I came here as a baby. I'm fully American.

02:21.200 --> 02:25.120
If you send me back to the Azores,
it'll be like serving a life sentence.

02:26.400 --> 02:27.680
Next!

03:17.000 --> 03:19.040
Eduardo, get over here!

03:25.160 --> 03:28.320
I don't wanna see your girlfriend's
filthy panties in my living room!

03:28.920 --> 03:30.560
Sílvia isn't my girlfriend, okay?

03:30.560 --> 03:34.160
Well, this isn't a goddamn pigsty.
Definitely not a hotel.

03:34.160 --> 03:35.280
One more thing.

03:35.960 --> 03:37.520
This moved since last night.

03:37.520 --> 03:39.640
I haven't touched anything, Uncle Joe.

03:41.400 --> 03:43.320
Be warned, all of you!

03:43.320 --> 03:45.120
No one touches my harpoon. Okay?

03:45.120 --> 03:47.120
Are we talking about your dick
or the harpoon?

03:47.800 --> 03:49.280
This harpoon was used in a film

03:49.280 --> 03:51.440
that Orson Welles shot
right by here in Faial.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.600
- No shit!
- Yes, shit.

03:53.600 --> 03:54.840
Called <i>Barbed Water.</i>

03:54.840 --> 03:57.080
My grandfather's in it,
harpooning a sperm whale.

03:57.080 --> 03:58.320
It's part of our story.

03:59.000 --> 04:01.560
Back when there were still real men
in the Azores.

04:06.320 --> 04:07.600
They're not mine. Hmm?

04:08.320 --> 04:09.360
Um...

04:10.240 --> 04:11.760
Sorry.

04:11.760 --> 04:13.080
Fuck me.

04:19.120 --> 04:21.080
Hey, hey, hey, hey! Don't do that!

04:21.600 --> 04:23.680
- It'll kill him.
- It's just a few crumbs.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.360
- No, no. Bread isn't edible to goldfish.
- Inedible?

04:26.360 --> 04:30.080
Otherwise, they'll inflate like a balloon,
and die. Come on, clean up the mess.

04:30.840 --> 04:33.520
You, come with me.
You have a good enough body to work.

04:34.080 --> 04:36.200
This body does more than that.

04:37.640 --> 04:38.640
Clean this mess.

04:43.320 --> 04:46.880
Mmm. Yo, this chorizo's really good.
Where do you get it?

04:48.240 --> 04:51.600
I make my own chorizo
with a special ingredient.

04:52.200 --> 04:54.160
They're really good.
What do you make them with?

04:54.680 --> 04:55.960
My chickens' shit.

04:57.640 --> 04:58.480
Delicious, right?

05:00.080 --> 05:01.080
What the fuck?

06:27.600 --> 06:28.920
America is that way.

06:29.520 --> 06:31.840
1,900 nautical miles to Boston.

06:42.040 --> 06:44.160
I still can't believe
that Rafael isn't here.

06:45.600 --> 06:47.960
- And that my dad could actually--
- Arruda's not your father.

06:49.920 --> 06:52.880
He's the man who knocked your mother up,
and didn't give a shit about you.

06:56.880 --> 06:59.680
Someday, we'll see
that fucker's coffin passing by us.

07:04.440 --> 07:06.840
Have you ever noticed
you keep looking for solutions?

07:09.200 --> 07:12.280
You don't feel well in Rabo de Peixe,
you want to go to America.

07:12.280 --> 07:15.280
Arruda killed Rafael,
so now he must die for it.

07:18.640 --> 07:20.680
Eduardo, I don't need solutions.

07:23.360 --> 07:25.160
I just need someone who'll listen.

07:27.920 --> 07:29.640
Rafael wasn't just your boyfriend.

07:32.320 --> 07:33.920
He was also my best friend.

07:42.720 --> 07:44.080
And I'll never forget him.

07:51.440 --> 07:53.240
But we have to move on, right?

07:56.560 --> 07:58.800
We all grieve in our own way, you know?

08:12.960 --> 08:16.360
What if the drugs we brought here
aren't a solution, but a problem?

09:25.720 --> 09:26.600
Detective.

09:27.120 --> 09:29.920
Perhaps this will help us
understand what happened here.

09:32.080 --> 09:35.400
We've also collected shell casings
and blood samples up near the lighthouse.

09:36.400 --> 09:37.520
Any witnesses?

09:37.520 --> 09:40.000
No witnesses.
No one's lived here in years.

09:40.000 --> 09:41.640
It's an automated lighthouse.

09:41.640 --> 09:43.200
And the nearest house is about...

09:44.440 --> 09:45.520
a mile from here.

09:46.800 --> 09:49.280
Didn't you say
nothing ever happens in São Miguel?

09:51.680 --> 09:52.920
I guess I was wrong.

09:57.360 --> 09:59.360
I don't want you here much longer, kid.

10:00.800 --> 10:02.480
I was never good as a babysitter.

10:03.920 --> 10:07.720
And I don't know what you've been up to,
but I don't want trouble on my end.

10:10.520 --> 10:12.680
I wanted to talk
about something, Uncle Joe.

10:15.440 --> 10:17.800
Uncle Joe, are you taking
my mom to America?

10:17.800 --> 10:19.400
Eduardo, go to your room.

10:24.320 --> 10:26.200
No need to be so hard on the kid.

10:26.200 --> 10:27.160
He's my son.

10:28.240 --> 10:29.480
He's my family too.

10:30.840 --> 10:32.640
And if you hadn't fled America,

10:32.640 --> 10:35.440
then my sister would be
receiving treatment in a decent hospital,

10:35.440 --> 10:37.480
with real doctors.
Ever thought about that?

10:37.480 --> 10:39.160
I didn't flee America.

10:39.160 --> 10:42.000
I had a family to raise back here.
You wouldn't get it, Joe.

10:47.800 --> 10:49.040
I want to go to America.

10:50.640 --> 10:51.840
Can you help me?

10:51.840 --> 10:55.120
Enough with going to America.
You think you're the only one?

10:56.080 --> 10:58.200
Every day, millions of idiots
around the world

10:58.760 --> 11:00.600
think they can make it there.

11:00.600 --> 11:04.360
The American dream.
It would be funny if it wasn't so stupid.

11:04.360 --> 11:05.600
But why is it stupid?

11:06.560 --> 11:09.560
- You lived there, and so did my dad.
- What's your last name, kid?

11:10.560 --> 11:11.400
Melo.

11:11.400 --> 11:13.240
Okay, that's reason number one.

11:13.240 --> 11:15.400
Portuguese name, puts you
at the bottom of the pyramid.

11:15.400 --> 11:16.760
What pyramid? What are you even--

11:16.760 --> 11:19.280
The pyramid of dicks
who will never make it over there.

11:19.800 --> 11:21.840
I've always considered myself an American.

11:21.840 --> 11:24.480
But my passport says what? "Portuguese."

11:25.400 --> 11:28.080
The game is rigged,
and I was fucked from the start.

11:28.600 --> 11:30.120
So wake the fuck up, for Christ's sake.

12:07.440 --> 12:09.160
Stupid birds.

12:12.600 --> 12:15.200
That's it. That's it!

12:16.280 --> 12:17.200
Go away!

12:19.440 --> 12:20.520
Go away!

12:39.360 --> 12:40.720
I think he might be dead.

12:46.760 --> 12:47.720
Are you okay?

12:57.720 --> 12:59.600
Out of the way!

13:00.120 --> 13:01.080
Move!

13:09.120 --> 13:11.440
He looks like the guy from <i>The Matrix.</i>

13:14.040 --> 13:15.040
Oh, shit!

13:31.200 --> 13:33.120
Okay, I'll wait for him here.

13:34.160 --> 13:35.720
Yes, don't worry.

13:36.600 --> 13:37.680
Bye, darling.

13:40.960 --> 13:43.400
Hey,
what are you doing there, eh?

13:44.040 --> 13:47.560
Listen.
Shall I give you a cigarette? Huh?

13:53.800 --> 13:55.160
Hey, hey!

13:55.760 --> 13:58.520
I wouldn't tell
your mother if I were you.

13:58.520 --> 13:59.640
Shh.

14:01.920 --> 14:03.560
Shut the kid up. I'm gonna lose my mind.

14:03.560 --> 14:05.960
He cries because he's realized
what kind of a man his dad is!

14:05.960 --> 14:06.880
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

14:06.880 --> 14:09.640
- There's no peace and quiet in this house!
- You're a fucking monk now?

14:09.640 --> 14:13.040
Okay, calm down.
Oh! Where are you going?

14:14.760 --> 14:19.640
Mamma mia!
Spaghetti with clams, so good!

14:20.840 --> 14:22.000
Mmm.

14:22.560 --> 14:26.200
You're a magnificent cook,
signora. Magnificent!

14:27.000 --> 14:30.080
Oh! Poor little guy. May I?

14:30.080 --> 14:33.440
Come here.
Poor little guy. Don't cry.

14:33.440 --> 14:35.760
There, there. It's okay.

14:45.480 --> 14:48.320
Family is
the most important thing in a man's life.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.040
You see? He's quiet now.

15:00.640 --> 15:01.680
Can I be the best man?

15:02.400 --> 15:03.240
Huh?

15:03.240 --> 15:05.040
So many years of being romantic confidant,

15:05.040 --> 15:07.120
I think I deserve
to be the best man, right?

15:07.120 --> 15:09.120
- Hmm?
- Rafael deserves respect.

15:10.680 --> 15:12.760
That's all you did
while he was alive, Eduardo.

15:13.840 --> 15:14.800
It's too soon.

15:16.600 --> 15:17.960
Hey there. Where you going?

15:18.680 --> 15:20.200
- The beach.
- Ah.

15:23.120 --> 15:25.520
Just make sure it's not too late, 'kay?

15:28.720 --> 15:31.120
Rafael promised to bring me here

15:31.120 --> 15:32.440
at least twice.

15:33.120 --> 15:36.560
He never cared to know
what I was thinking or was feeling.

15:38.360 --> 15:39.600
What my dreams were.

15:43.160 --> 15:44.800
To him, I was just a trophy.

16:00.560 --> 16:02.680
You're the most amazing woman that I know.

16:05.120 --> 16:06.760
And what other girls do you know?

16:06.760 --> 16:09.280
You've never left Rabo de Peixe. And look.

16:11.320 --> 16:13.800
I'm the only girl around for miles.

16:17.280 --> 16:18.480
I've seen women in movies.

16:21.920 --> 16:24.040
Okay, so if I'm so incredible,

16:24.560 --> 16:26.640
why hasn't anyone ever proposed to me?

16:26.640 --> 16:27.600
Hmm?

16:29.320 --> 16:33.120
You men, you're total cowards.
That's the truth.

16:41.200 --> 16:42.360
Sorry, Joe.

16:43.880 --> 16:45.400
"A Change Is Gonna Come."

16:47.800 --> 16:50.080
It was the first song
I learned to play on the piano.

16:50.080 --> 16:52.880
An advocate of the civil rights
here on the island.

16:54.120 --> 16:57.040
Some pains are from everywhere.
They have no borders, Joe.

16:57.040 --> 16:58.280
Yep.

17:03.600 --> 17:04.440
What are yours?

17:04.440 --> 17:06.840
You don't really care
about my pains, do you?

17:07.440 --> 17:08.800
Let me guess. You're different.

17:09.400 --> 17:10.440
Don't ridicule me.

17:10.440 --> 17:11.480
I'm not.

17:14.880 --> 17:16.400
I've been around, know what I'm saying?

17:16.400 --> 17:19.760
Grew up in the '60s.
Made myself a man in the '70s.

17:20.360 --> 17:21.720
Spent seven years in jail.

17:23.480 --> 17:24.520
I respect who you are.

17:28.000 --> 17:30.080
You know why I keep
this harpoon here in the house?

17:31.160 --> 17:33.280
Because knowing who you are
is as important

17:34.440 --> 17:35.920
as knowing who you're not.

17:38.480 --> 17:39.960
So the question is...

17:42.080 --> 17:44.560
are we gonna sit here like two lame dicks,

17:44.560 --> 17:47.920
or are we going to listen
to some fucking great music, huh?

18:12.720 --> 18:14.920
If I proposed to you right now,
what would you say?

18:16.720 --> 18:18.920
"You're out of your mind."

18:33.280 --> 18:34.920
Third time's the charm.

18:57.160 --> 18:59.640
So she's your girlfriend after all.

19:00.720 --> 19:02.920
Take it easy, all right?

19:03.960 --> 19:05.800
Look. Uncle Joe, look at that!

19:05.800 --> 19:07.080
I already got one.

19:08.680 --> 19:10.120
Here it is.

19:10.120 --> 19:12.640
Right? Huh?

19:13.960 --> 19:18.280
Who you gonna feed with this shit?
Makes no fucking sense. Too much work.

19:18.280 --> 19:21.000
- My technique is way more efficient, okay?
- Let's do it.

19:25.320 --> 19:26.840
Do you have any ketchup?

19:28.040 --> 19:29.240
We don't eat that crap here.

19:29.840 --> 19:31.240
What's ketchup, Uncle Joe?

19:31.240 --> 19:33.920
Mmm. Ketchup is one of the best things
in the world,

19:33.920 --> 19:35.480
but your dad doesn't know it.

19:36.840 --> 19:38.440
Dad, can I taste ketchup?

19:39.960 --> 19:42.240
I'll send you some
when I get back to America, okay?

19:43.400 --> 19:45.280
Don't give him any stupid ideas, please.

19:45.280 --> 19:46.960
It's only ketchup.

19:46.960 --> 19:49.000
I'm not afraid to compete
in America, all right?

19:49.000 --> 19:50.880
- No, that's not it, kid.
- Well, then?

19:53.000 --> 19:53.920
The truth is,

19:54.760 --> 19:57.320
you've dreamed of going to America
since you were a child.

19:58.080 --> 20:00.000
I kind of feel responsible for it.

20:01.640 --> 20:03.640
You know, you never sent
that ketchup you promised.

20:03.640 --> 20:05.640
Well, before I knew it, I was in jail.

20:06.800 --> 20:08.240
Priorities change, right?

20:10.040 --> 20:12.280
- You know your fish, Red?
- Yep.

20:12.280 --> 20:14.240
He's always gonna live in that fishbowl.

20:14.240 --> 20:17.120
Of course.
And he'll be happy. He's a goldfish.

20:17.120 --> 20:19.800
Well, if I stay here,
I'll never be anything.

20:20.560 --> 20:22.480
I'm just a fish stuck in a fishbowl.
You follow?

20:24.400 --> 20:27.440
In America,
you'll be a small fish in a huge pond.

20:28.560 --> 20:31.040
Here, at least,
Red has food and a place to live.

20:33.960 --> 20:35.600
I don't want to go back home.

20:36.280 --> 20:38.000
You don't want to or you can't?

20:51.000 --> 20:53.000
You'll need to leave very soon, kid.

20:54.360 --> 20:55.600
They'll come for this.

20:56.200 --> 20:57.200
They always do.

21:08.400 --> 21:09.520
I'm fucking seeing a camel!

21:10.360 --> 21:11.880
Dude, come on, I promise you.

21:11.880 --> 21:14.040
- I'm really seeing a camel.
- Yeah, yeah, me too.

21:14.040 --> 21:16.240
I'm seeing a camel.
Look over there, with ten humps.

21:16.240 --> 21:17.960
Oh, look who's all wasted.

21:17.960 --> 21:20.160
You're the one
who's completely wasted, okay?

21:20.160 --> 21:22.840
And you'll wind up cross-eyed
playing your little <i>Snake</i> game there.

21:22.840 --> 21:24.400
How, like this? Hmm?

21:24.400 --> 21:26.880
Don't I look pretty like this?

21:26.880 --> 21:29.440
It's time to release the prisoner.

21:31.480 --> 21:32.520
Mmm.

21:32.520 --> 21:35.320
Guys, did you know
that the police can use a cell phone

21:35.320 --> 21:36.840
to track a person?

21:38.000 --> 21:40.440
- What are you talking about?
- I saw it once on the news.

21:42.160 --> 21:43.280
Are you serious?

21:43.280 --> 21:46.280
Goodbye, little snake.
I'll miss you so much.

21:57.160 --> 21:59.040
Oh!

22:00.080 --> 22:03.480
Only the stars know
where the fuck we are now!

22:05.200 --> 22:06.560
Whoo!

22:08.880 --> 22:10.000
Hey, hey, hey!

22:10.000 --> 22:11.200
Hey!

22:11.200 --> 22:12.840
I brought the good stuff!

22:13.760 --> 22:16.440
It even puts hair on your chest.

22:16.440 --> 22:17.840
Now, hear me out.

22:19.000 --> 22:20.720
Who wants to blow some shit up?

22:22.920 --> 22:23.840
No.

22:27.000 --> 22:29.960
Fuck, I swear, man. This fucking shit
weighs more than Dolly Parton's tits.

22:29.960 --> 22:32.520
- I wouldn't know about it.
- Come on, push.

22:32.520 --> 22:35.200
Let's go down. Go back. Come on, one, two.

22:39.400 --> 22:40.400
Come on.

22:40.920 --> 22:41.920
All right!

22:48.320 --> 22:49.520
You do the honors.

22:59.040 --> 23:00.120
Whoa!

23:03.120 --> 23:04.280
That was amazing!

23:06.840 --> 23:07.800
Come here!

23:09.200 --> 23:12.280
- Hey, hey, hey! Hold it!
- Sorry, haven't got excited in a minute.

23:12.280 --> 23:14.600
Sorry.

23:14.600 --> 23:18.920
You know what? Come on, kid.
Blowing shit up makes me hungry.

23:38.400 --> 23:40.760
- You sure you don't want to marry me?
- No, never.

23:40.760 --> 23:42.200
- No?
- Mmm.

23:42.200 --> 23:44.760
- Shall we not marry in America?
- Let's not.

23:50.560 --> 23:52.800
I always liked you. You know that, right?

24:28.840 --> 24:30.680
Love makes great music.

24:32.320 --> 24:34.840
But it doesn't always bring
two different worlds together.

24:34.840 --> 24:36.560
That's how I put it.

24:38.200 --> 24:39.800
Tell me about it.

24:40.600 --> 24:43.200
What? Did you also fall in love
with a Black Panther

24:43.200 --> 24:44.200
pursued by the FBI?

24:45.720 --> 24:47.160
No, no, no. Much better!

24:47.760 --> 24:50.120
Now you've got my full attention. Go on.

24:56.200 --> 24:57.960
The priest in Rabo de Peixe.

25:04.040 --> 25:06.280
