25:07.800 --> 25:08.840
Why "misfortune"?

25:08.840 --> 25:09.920
He's a priest.

25:12.560 --> 25:14.840
I, on the other hand, am... you know.

25:15.360 --> 25:16.680
Uh-huh.

25:17.480 --> 25:19.360
Haven't you just told me
that not even love

25:19.360 --> 25:21.480
can bring two people
from different worlds together?

25:23.840 --> 25:25.360
And what do I know about love?

25:28.560 --> 25:30.680
I live alone on an island...

25:32.440 --> 25:33.920
in the middle of nowhere.

25:36.440 --> 25:39.520
There is one very important thing
that I am sure of.

25:40.560 --> 25:41.600
And that is...

25:42.840 --> 25:43.680
Yes?

25:45.400 --> 25:47.040
- Joe.
- Hmm?

25:47.680 --> 25:51.040
You said, "One very important thing
I'm sure of." What's the answer?

25:53.440 --> 25:54.520
I forgot.

26:49.360 --> 26:50.640
Where is your son?

26:51.600 --> 26:53.000
You know I won't tell you that.

26:54.160 --> 26:55.880
I could let you live.

26:56.960 --> 26:59.520
What kind of father
wants to survive his son?

27:05.960 --> 27:06.960
I'm ready.

27:10.200 --> 27:11.360
So am I.

27:31.840 --> 27:33.400
<i>I can hear your heart.</i>

27:36.280 --> 27:37.800
<i>But I don't know what it says.</i>

27:42.760 --> 27:44.120
<i>It said the same thing.</i>

27:45.280 --> 27:46.360
<i>For years.</i>

27:51.160 --> 27:52.760
<i>I'm not talking about us.</i>

27:53.800 --> 27:55.280
<i>I'm talking about you</i>.

27:56.880 --> 27:59.880
<i>At school, the guys used to say
that you were the Submarine.</i>

28:01.240 --> 28:02.800
<i>Like that was a good thing.</i>

28:03.640 --> 28:05.440
<i>But I'm not so sure it is.</i>

28:07.920 --> 28:09.400
<i>As if you were always hiding...</i>

28:10.840 --> 28:11.960
<i>or running away.</i>

28:12.960 --> 28:14.600
<i>As if you were never really here.</i>

28:14.600 --> 28:15.840
<i>Don't run away.</i>

28:17.040 --> 28:19.440
<i>I'll give you something
that'll be just yours.</i>

28:20.160 --> 28:21.400
<i>Something real.</i>

28:23.560 --> 28:26.800
<i>My mother,
she didn't want me to see her like that.</i>

28:28.520 --> 28:29.920
<i>So I hid under her bed.</i>

28:32.560 --> 28:35.320
<i>I don't know.
It was like-- like I could protect her.</i>

28:37.240 --> 28:38.400
<i>On the night she died,</i>

28:39.200 --> 28:42.560
<i>she told my father that I could sleep
beside her on the bed.</i>

28:46.600 --> 28:47.840
<i>I didn't open my eyes.</i>

28:49.800 --> 28:51.160
It still haunts me.

28:51.160 --> 28:52.080
I mean...

28:55.600 --> 28:57.520
I should have kept my eyes open.

29:00.480 --> 29:02.200
I should have looked at my mother.

29:04.160 --> 29:05.840
To see her for the last time.

29:37.080 --> 29:39.760
Detective, come take a look at something.

29:44.800 --> 29:47.320
These are pricey shoes
for a fisherman from Rabo de Peixe.

29:52.960 --> 29:56.160
No one knows where Eduardo is,
and his friends are also missing.

29:57.200 --> 29:59.600
Well, they must have run
like hell.

30:00.880 --> 30:04.720
Perhaps Detective Banha
knows their whereabouts. No?

30:09.160 --> 30:10.880
I told you. I barely know them.

30:11.480 --> 30:12.520
Mm-hmm.

30:17.600 --> 30:18.560
Look, Bruna.

30:19.200 --> 30:21.560
I really believe
you don't know where they are.

30:22.800 --> 30:25.000
But I'm also sure
you have some information.

30:26.120 --> 30:27.800
Cooperation will help.

30:30.640 --> 30:33.240
You want my help
to arrest some kids from Rabo de Peixe?

30:35.600 --> 30:38.320
I'm gonna tell you something
I learned since I got here.

30:41.280 --> 30:43.080
What did you bring my daughter in for?

30:44.040 --> 30:46.520
- We're just going over some things.
- Not anymore, Frias.

30:46.520 --> 30:47.480
Let's go, Bruna.

31:23.480 --> 31:25.200
Where is Francesco Bonino?

31:56.240 --> 31:57.480
- Good morning!
- Mmm.

31:59.200 --> 32:02.080
Joe, how are you so fresh
after what you drank yesterday?

32:02.080 --> 32:03.640
I'm a real man.

32:04.560 --> 32:07.080
You know what's good for a hangover?
Fried liver.

32:09.000 --> 32:12.640
I swear by everything sacred,
I'll never touch another drop of alcohol.

32:13.640 --> 32:16.920
Yeah, I've heard that one before.
Now, will you go get my mail?

32:17.680 --> 32:19.120
Box 36.

32:53.240 --> 32:56.040
Where the hell are you, you little shit?
I'm worried sick.

32:57.240 --> 32:59.840
You're right. I'm sorry, Mom.
Don't worry, everything's fine.

33:03.520 --> 33:05.720
I should smack you across the face
with a parakeet.

33:05.720 --> 33:08.280
Either you tell me where you are,
or your birds are gonna starve.

33:13.080 --> 33:14.480
Something terrible happened.

33:28.800 --> 33:29.640
Eduardo.

33:32.200 --> 33:33.440
We need to talk.

33:36.400 --> 33:38.640
- I need to go to Rabo de Peixe!
- Eduardo, wait!

33:38.640 --> 33:40.560
- You can't go back--
- Don't you get it?

33:40.560 --> 33:42.920
- I have to go back to bury my father!
- I didn't bury Rafael.

33:42.920 --> 33:44.920
I don't even know
where his body is, and I'm here.

33:44.920 --> 33:46.640
Eduardo, Sílvia's right.
You can't go back.

33:46.640 --> 33:50.320
All you're gonna do is fuck up the plan.
I told your father I'd help you,

33:50.320 --> 33:51.960
and that's what I'm gonna do.

33:52.440 --> 33:54.080
- What plan?
- America.

33:54.080 --> 33:55.680
Isn't that what you all want?

33:55.680 --> 33:57.840
What plan
is he talking about?

33:57.840 --> 34:00.640
It doesn't matter anymore, Sílvia,
because as of now, the fucking--

34:00.640 --> 34:03.720
Until you're far away, there won't
be peace, with or without cocaine.

34:03.720 --> 34:05.560
Your father didn't just die of old age.

34:06.320 --> 34:09.320
I know that. And that's why
I'm gonna kill the motherfucker.

34:10.000 --> 34:11.320
- Eduardo!
- Kid!

34:11.320 --> 34:12.560
Kid!

34:13.640 --> 34:15.240
Where do you think you're going?

34:18.400 --> 34:20.080
Leave me the fuck alone!

34:24.880 --> 34:25.800
They're the Mafia.

34:27.440 --> 34:29.400
You don't kill them. They kill you.

34:30.240 --> 34:33.200
I'm gonna help you,
but I need you to calm the fuck down!

34:33.800 --> 34:34.680
Do you hear?

34:38.760 --> 34:39.640
Attaboy.

35:02.840 --> 35:05.880
Hello, my little ones.

35:05.880 --> 35:09.400
Come on. All right, all right,
let's calm down. Let's calm down.

35:09.400 --> 35:11.680
Come on, come on.

35:11.680 --> 35:13.360
Such a good boy.

35:18.640 --> 35:19.720
Come back here!

35:20.680 --> 35:21.880
Oh, no. Shit.

35:22.800 --> 35:25.520
Come on, little bird,
come back here. Come eat.

35:26.360 --> 35:27.200
Oh.

35:27.200 --> 35:30.440
Hello, little bird. Come on.
Eat something, my little bird.

35:30.440 --> 35:31.680
Look here.

35:31.680 --> 35:34.080
Look here, eat it. Okay, go ahead, eat.

35:45.600 --> 35:46.640
How weird.

35:47.680 --> 35:48.720
I never...

35:49.960 --> 35:52.200
thought these little birds would be...

35:53.440 --> 35:54.760
so easy to break.

36:03.040 --> 36:05.080
Eduardo!

36:05.080 --> 36:06.080
Did you hear that?

36:06.640 --> 36:08.480
- And so it begins.
- What's happening?

36:08.480 --> 36:10.080
Go and cover Red's fishbowl.

36:10.080 --> 36:12.640
Eduardo!

36:20.440 --> 36:23.920
We actually have
two ways to settle this, fuckers!

36:23.920 --> 36:25.200
Go, go.

36:25.720 --> 36:26.880
The first one,

36:26.880 --> 36:29.880
now you give me
the shit that is rightfully mine,

36:30.680 --> 36:32.480
and I leave this place in peace.

36:35.000 --> 36:36.160
Or go with the second option--

36:39.360 --> 36:40.760
Who's this asshole?

36:41.320 --> 36:44.480
I'm option number two, motherfucker!

36:45.080 --> 36:46.320
Oh, if it isn't Wednesday.

36:46.320 --> 36:48.920
But there's a third option,
you fucking piece of shit.

36:48.920 --> 36:51.360
You take your stooges
and get the fuck out of here.

36:51.960 --> 36:53.880
The drugs aren't yours and never were.

36:54.960 --> 36:55.840
Oh!

36:56.440 --> 36:58.600
Hello, you sly little girl.

36:59.760 --> 37:00.880
You really had me going, huh?

37:00.880 --> 37:03.680
And you were the weakest
of them all, fucker.

37:04.280 --> 37:06.280
At least Rafael had balls,
you know, you little shit?

37:06.280 --> 37:07.560
And you killed him, you fucker!

37:07.560 --> 37:09.760
No, you're the reason Rafael's dead!

37:09.760 --> 37:12.080
Come on, get inside now! Come on!

37:12.080 --> 37:13.120
Go, go! Come on!

37:14.440 --> 37:15.520
Stay down, stay down!

37:15.520 --> 37:17.920
Get the fuck in there, for fuck's sake!
Get in there, go!

37:21.840 --> 37:23.440
Get the fuck inside, come on!

37:23.440 --> 37:25.400
Ah, for fuck's sake!

37:25.400 --> 37:26.640
Go, go!

37:40.800 --> 37:43.200
What are you waiting for?
You can go in now, asshole! Come on!

37:43.200 --> 37:44.200
Go, go!

37:45.560 --> 37:48.040
That filthy motherfucker!

37:54.320 --> 37:55.440
Fuck!

38:06.480 --> 38:08.280
You motherfuckers!

38:20.360 --> 38:21.640
Where are the fucking drugs?

38:21.640 --> 38:24.440
Huh? I'll blow your fucking head off,
do you understand?

38:24.440 --> 38:26.160
Where are the fucking drugs?

38:26.160 --> 38:27.680
- Answer me!
- Let him fucking go.

38:32.920 --> 38:35.480
Hey, you have to be careful
with that shit. That's not a BB gun.

38:35.480 --> 38:37.560
- It's got one hell of a kick.
- Get out of here!

38:37.560 --> 38:38.600
Please. Look.

38:40.560 --> 38:41.400
Zinha.

38:41.400 --> 38:44.000
Because of the fucking cocaine,
you almost died.

38:44.000 --> 38:46.520
Who was by your side?
Who took care of you?

38:48.120 --> 38:48.960
Your father.

38:49.880 --> 38:53.640
I took care of you.
Baby girl, tell me where the drugs are.

38:55.640 --> 38:57.280
And we'll go home, you and I.

38:57.280 --> 38:58.400
I'm your father.

38:59.040 --> 39:00.280
And you're my daughter.

39:01.520 --> 39:02.760
All can be forgiven.

39:03.400 --> 39:05.480
Huh? All right, Zinha?

39:05.480 --> 39:06.680
"Zinha," fucking shit!

39:08.240 --> 39:10.160
You fucking traitor!

39:10.160 --> 39:13.040
You want to kill your fucking father?
What's wrong with you?

39:13.040 --> 39:14.960
You traitor!

39:18.840 --> 39:20.120
You fucking traitor!

39:22.040 --> 39:23.440
Fuck...

39:29.240 --> 39:31.720
Fuck.

39:44.360 --> 39:45.720
It was you or him, kid.

39:46.760 --> 39:48.160
I'm glad it was him.

40:04.080 --> 40:05.280
What's next?

40:10.840 --> 40:12.160
We're lucky to be alive.

40:18.880 --> 40:20.640
There's no excuse for what I did.

40:25.840 --> 40:27.400
But at least we got justice.

40:30.920 --> 40:33.920
For Rafael
and for all the fucked up shit Arruda did.

40:47.400 --> 40:49.680
Neither of us have
a clear conscience anymore.

40:57.480 --> 41:01.280
No one forced us
to keep the drugs, that was our decision.

41:10.560 --> 41:11.400
Eduardo.

41:20.320 --> 41:21.720
We chose this path.

41:26.160 --> 41:27.080
No.

41:29.360 --> 41:30.600
It's not that simple.

41:34.120 --> 41:36.240
Sometimes you gotta get your hands dirty.

41:44.560 --> 41:48.000
I mean, it wasn't just Arruda
who died today.

41:50.880 --> 41:53.560
I'm gonna have to carry his death
for the rest of my life.

41:55.720 --> 41:56.600
I know.

42:21.160 --> 42:23.360
Never let the dead
take their gold to the grave.

42:23.360 --> 42:24.760
They won't need it.

42:25.920 --> 42:27.880
You learn a lot when you're in the can.

42:28.840 --> 42:30.320
I should make you a list.

42:31.200 --> 42:34.080
Because you'll probably end up in jail.
Or killed.

42:34.600 --> 42:36.880
You're not in prison or dead, all right?

42:37.720 --> 42:39.440
This is a prison by the ocean.

42:40.720 --> 42:42.320
Or a cemetery for the living.

42:43.480 --> 42:45.320
I won't get locked up or buried.

42:46.360 --> 42:49.080
We had a plan, and if we follow it,
everything will be all right.

42:49.600 --> 42:51.360
- What about your girlfriend?
- She's not my--

42:51.360 --> 42:53.760
What about your fucking girlfriend?

42:57.880 --> 43:00.000
She wants to get rid of the coke
and get out of here.

43:01.880 --> 43:03.560
That's just fucking stupid.

43:03.560 --> 43:06.840
You do that, and your life
will be exactly like your father's--

43:06.840 --> 43:10.400
Then what the fuck am I supposed to do?
Just tell me, please!

43:11.040 --> 43:13.240
I go, I end up like you.
I stay, I end up like my father.

43:13.240 --> 43:15.120
What's the right choice? Just tell me!

43:17.640 --> 43:19.320
There's no right choice.

43:20.400 --> 43:22.160
You can go back to Rabo de Peixe

43:22.160 --> 43:24.720
and be a small fish
in a small pond all your life.

43:25.600 --> 43:28.840
Or you can take a leap of faith
and risk getting caught or killed.

43:31.400 --> 43:32.280
Listen, kid.

43:34.480 --> 43:36.680
You and I,
we were cut from the same cloth.

43:37.520 --> 43:40.240
We didn't come to this world
to live boring lives.

43:41.400 --> 43:43.800
It all comes down to this.

43:43.800 --> 43:46.440
Get busy living or get busy dying.

43:48.120 --> 43:50.160
So let's get fucking busy already.

43:50.160 --> 43:52.000
I'll get you to America.

43:52.000 --> 43:53.160
But I want my cut.

43:53.800 --> 43:55.800
Of course you do.

